      "firm_id": "sybil_9",
      "description": "Presented is a museum-grade 2001 BMW M3, a pinnacle of naturally aspirated engineering. At its heart lies the S54 3.2L inline-six, featuring individual throttle bodies and high-pressure VANOS, delivering linear power up to an 8,000 RPM redline. This example features the desirable Getrag 6-speed manual transmission and a variable M differential lock for surgical power delivery. The chassis is structurally flawless, with documented subframe reinforcement and refreshed bushings maintaining factory suspension geometry. Finished in Laguna Seca Blue with an immaculate interior, this E46 remains in its original, unmodified configuration, offering a pure mechanical connection and peerless performance.",
